/--
Given a set `S` and an element `b` in an order `Œ≤`, where all intervals bounded above are finite,
we define the partial density of `S` (relative to a set `A`) to be the proportion of elements in
`{x ‚àà A | x < b}` that lie in `S ‚à© A`.

This definition was inspired from https://github.com/b-mehta/unit-fractions
-/
noncomputable abbrev partialDensity {Œ≤ : Type*} [Preorder Œ≤] [LocallyFiniteOrderBot Œ≤]
    (S : Set Œ≤) (A : Set Œ≤ := Set.univ) (b : Œ≤) : ‚Ñù :=
  (S ‚à© A ‚à© Set.Iio b).ncard / (A ‚à© Set.Iio b).ncard

/--
Given a set `S` in an order `Œ≤`, where all intervals bounded above are finite, we define the upper
density of `S` (relative to a set `A`) to be the limsup of the partial densities of `S`
(relative to `A`) for `b ‚Üí ‚àû`.
-/
noncomputable def upperDensity {Œ≤ : Type*} [Preorder Œ≤] [LocallyFiniteOrderBot Œ≤]
    (S : Set Œ≤) (A : Set Œ≤ := Set.univ) : ‚Ñù :=
  atTop.limsup (fun (b : Œ≤) ‚Ü¶ S.partialDensity A b)

/--
Given a set `S` in an order `Œ≤`, where all intervals bounded above are finite, we define the lower
density of `S` (relative to a set `A`) to be the liminf of the partial densities of `S`
(relative to `A`) for `b ‚Üí ‚àû`.
-/
noncomputable def lowerDensity {Œ≤ : Type*} [Preorder Œ≤] [LocallyFiniteOrderBot Œ≤]
    (S : Set Œ≤) (A : Set Œ≤ := Set.univ) : ‚Ñù :=
  atTop.liminf (fun (b : Œ≤) ‚Ü¶ S.partialDensity A b)

/--
A set `S` in an order `Œ≤` where all intervals bounded above are finite is said to have
density `Œ± : ‚Ñù` (relative to a set `A`) if the proportion of `x ‚àà S` such that `x < n`
in `A` tends to `Œ±` as `n ‚Üí ‚àû`.

When `Œ≤ = ‚Ñï` this by default defines the natural density of a set
(i.e., relative to all of `‚Ñï`).
-/
def HasDensity {Œ≤ : Type*} [Preorder Œ≤] [LocallyFiniteOrderBot Œ≤]
    (S : Set Œ≤) (Œ± : ‚Ñù) (A : Set Œ≤ := Set.univ) : Prop :=
  Tendsto (fun (b : Œ≤) => S.partialDensity A b) atTop (ùìù Œ±)

/--
A set `S` in an order `Œ≤` where all intervals bounded above are finite is said to have
positive density (relative to a set `A`) if there exists a positive `Œ± : ‚Ñù` such that
`S` has density `Œ±` (relative to a set `A`).
-/
def HasPosDensity {Œ≤ : Type*} [Preorder Œ≤] [LocallyFiniteOrderBot Œ≤]
    (S : Set Œ≤) (A : Set Œ≤ := Set.univ) : Prop :=
  ‚àÉ Œ± > 0, S.HasDensity Œ± A

